DPBlkflInd.description:

 A  Bulk filed and returned with statement; exception reasons disregarded. 
 B  Bulk filed and returned with statement; exception reasons cause items to outsort.  
 C  Fine sorted daily and returned with statement.  
 I  Image file (only for institutions using image statements).  
 N  Bulk file with cycle sort.

DPPerdcFeeCde.description: Service charge code to be used in the assessment of periodic fees.  If left blank, will default to Bank Control.

DPExcpPlnNbr.description: Represents a set of exception processing options and defaults, as defined on Product Control of the Exceptions Desktop.  Only available for use by institutions that have converted to Exceptions Desktop.

EscrowSubAcctPln.description: Number that identifies the DESA plan assigned to the account.

DPAnlysCycCde.description: Cycle code or table code that controls when analysis for interest payment and service charging occurs.  See your institution's Bank Control for selection.  If left blank, will default to Bank Control Cycle Segment 235 or Cycle Table Segment 236, depending on the value on the Account Option Segment.

DPFedTaxId.description:
Type of taxpayer number assigned to account.  If left blank, the field will default to N.  
 F  Federal Tax Number
 N  No Number  
 S  Social Security Number  
 T  Individual Taxpayer Identification Number

DPExtTrsfrTypCde.description:

DPTrckCde.description: Tracking code assigned to the account by your financial institution.

Maximum posting switch status codes:  1.  Maximum special transaction status codes:  3.  Maximum status codes:  4.  Note:  To add dormant status to an account, a keyword, DORMNT, must be performed.

WthAmtLbl.description: Used for override processing. Resubmit using the value returned here.

DPTDRATxnCde.description: Retirement account transaction code.  Must be compatible with deposit transaction code.  Required for retirement accounts.

ActnLbl.description: Used for override processing.  Resubmit using the value returned here.

WthTxnDesc.description: Used for override processing. Resubmit using the value returned here.

Designates whether the hold should be assigned if the hold amount is greater than the available balance.  
 Y  Assign hold regardless of balance.  
 Blank  Hold must be less than current balance.

Hold type.

DPHldDesc.description: The description of the hold or reason for the hold.

DPHAHldDelInd.description:
Indicates when hold will be deleted.  
 A  Hold will be deleted after posting.  
 B  Hold will be deleted before posting.  
 P  Hold was flagged during batch processing to be deleted the next day.

DPTxnMsg.description: Information about the status of this transaction.

DPStpPmtWaiveServChrgInd.description:

 Y  Waive service charge.

 1  All posted checks/ACH debits.

 3  Single check/ACH debit with matching amount.

ApplNbr.description: The application number of the account being updated.

ApplCde.description: The application code of the account being updated.

DPNmeAndAddrTinOwnr.description: Identifies which line of the name/address record contains the name of the person whose taxpayer identification number is on the account.  If left blank, defaults to 1.

DupStmtInd.description:
Determines whether a duplicate statement should be created for a deposit account.  
 M  Create a duplicate statement for a DESA subsidiary account and print the master account's name and address.  
 Y  Yes, create a duplicate statement using an alternate address.  
 Space  Do not create a duplicate statement.

DPCIRqstInd.description: For banks that use CIS, a Y must be entered here to allow updates to Name/Address Type 1.

Dup1099Ind.description:
Determines whether a duplicate 1099-INT form should be created for a deposit account.  
 M  Create a duplicate 1099-INT form for a DESA subsidiary account and print the master account's name and address.  
 Y  Yes, create a duplicate 1099-INT form using an alternate address.  
 Space  Do not create a duplicate 1099-INT form.

DPNmeAndAddrTyp.description:
Name and address type.  Required for deletes.  
 1  Regular (Default)  
 2  Analysis.  Used for Account Analysis statements.   Accounts must be set up on Account Analysis.  
 3-5  Other  
 8  Employer Address (Keogh) 
 9  Money Transfer Confirmations

DPNmeAndAddrStmtCpys.description: Number of statement copies to be produced.  Required for Name and Address Type 2.  Note:  Zero is valid for Name and Address Types 3, 4, and 5.

DPNmeAndAddrLne1.description: Name/Address Line 1.  Required for updates.  The ZIP code must be included in the city, state line.  A line should not be left blank between two valid lines.  Retirement accounts are limited to three lines of name and address information to meet government reporting regulations.

DupODNotice.description:
Determines whether a duplicate R-3112 overdraft notice should be created for a deposit account.  
 M  Create a duplicate R-3112 overdraft notice for a DESA subsidiary account and print the master account's name and address.  
 Y  Yes, create a duplicate R-3112 overdraft notice using an alternate address.  
 Space  Do not create a duplicate R-3112 overdraft notice.

DPNewCDLogTyp.description: Log type.  Leave blank for new certificates.  Enter R for intraday reversals.

DPNewCDPrinTrsfrToAcct.description: Number of the account receiving the transferred principal amount.

DPNewCDTxnSecurityInd.description:
Used only if using the selective security override method of exception handling.  Code authorizing you to override error and alert messages and to gain access to employee records.  If you wish to override, resubmit the transaction with the value returned here.  
 1  Alert override.  
 2  Operator override.  
 3  Supervisor override.

DPNewCDIntFreq.description: Length of interest term in days, months, or cycle.  Cycle can only be used with Level 4 certificates of deposit.  Value in DP Time Deposit Interest Frequency Indicator indicates what this number refers to.

DPNewCDTerm.description: Length of deposit in number of days or months.  Value in DP Time Deposit Term Indicator indicates whether this number refers to days or months.

DPNewCDTxnDte.description: Original deposit date.  If not entered, will default to next posting date of bank. Format YYYY-MM-DD.

DPNewCDGLAcctNbrOfst.description: The general ledger offset account number to be debited for institutions using on-line dollar interface.

DPNewCDIntBasisCdeDay.description:
Number of days per year used for calculating interest.  This field can default to Bank Control.  
 S  Actual/360 days.  
 T  Actual/365 days.  
 E  360/360 days (recalculate on interest date).  
 A  Actual days/actual days.  
 D  360/360 days (daily accrual).

DPNewCDCurIntRte.description: Rate of interest for certificate.  Length allows for decimal point and three decimal places with a maximum rate of 36.000.  This field can default to Bank Control.

DPNewCDGLCstCntrOfst.description: The cost center of the general ledger offset account number that is credited for institutions using on-line dollar interface.

DPNewCDIntPln.description: Interest plan.  See your Bank Control for selection.  If left blank, it will default to the account type interest plan.

DPNewCDOidInd.description: Indicates whether this is an Original Issue Discount account.  Y or N.

DPNewCDIssAmt.description: Original deposit amount.  Field length includes room for commas and a decimal point.  The actual amount is limited to one billion dollars minus one cent.

DPNewCDTermInd.description: Indicates whether value in DP Time Deposit Term refers to days (D) or months (M).

DPNewCDTrlrDesc1.description: Descriptive trailer to be stored with transaction.

DPNewCDPrinDpstnExtTrsfrTypCde.description:
Indicates the type of account receiving the principal disposition external transfer.  
 D  Deposit account.  
 G  General ledger account.  
 L  Loan account.  
 S  Savings account.

DPNewCDFnlMatDte.description: Final maturity date of this certificate.   Must be left blank for renewable certificates.  This field should be allowed to default. Format YYYY-MM-DD.

DPNewCDRetAcctTxnCde.description: RA code must be entered for retirement accounts.  Must be compatible with deposit transaction code.  If this is a reversal transaction, this will be the original RA code.

DPNewCDOvrideInfo.description: Used only if using the selective security override method of exception handling.  If you wish to override, resubmit the transaction with the value returned here.

DPNewCDTrlrDesc4.description: Descriptive trailer to be stored with transaction.

DPNewCDTrlrDesc3.description: Descriptive trailer to be stored with transaction.

DPNewCDTrlrDesc2.description: Descriptive trailer to be stored with transaction.

DPNewCDPmtMeth.description:
Method used to pay accrued interest.  If left blank, will default to Bank Control.  
 A  Add on.  
 C  Check.  
 T  Transfer.  
 R  Transfer (memo) (on-line teller banks only).  
 X  External transfer - ACH (future use).

DPNewCDId.description: Time deposit ID number.  If a certificate number is not entered, the system will assign a number.  The first certificate opened for an account will be assigned 001.  The number will increment by one for each additional certificate opened.

DPNewCDTxnCntlNbr.description: Control number.  Must be numeric and entered for intraday reversals.  Can be found on Today's On-Line Transaction Inquiry screen.

DPNewCDPnltyFrml.description:
Code for penalty formula used for withdrawal of funds.  This field can default to Bank Control.  
 000  No penalty.  
 001  Minimum regulation penalty.  
 002  7 day penalty.  
 003  3 month/6 month penalty.  
 006  Interest earned penalty. 
 007  6 month simple interest penalty.

DPNewCDPrinDpstnOpt.description:
Indicates how the principal amount will be distributed when a Level 3 time deposit, Level 4 certificate of deposit, or repurchase agreement account matures.  The entire principal or a portion of the principal can be renewed, distributed by check, or transferred to a Level 0 (DDA, NOW, savings, or money market) account.  

 Internal:  
 0  Do not distribute principal.  
 1  Renew fixed principal amount; issue check for remainder.  
 2  Renew fixed principal amount; transfer remainder.  
 3  Issue check for fixed principal amount; renew remainder.  
 4  Transfer fixed principal amount; renew remainder.  
 5  Issue check for fixed principal amount; transfer remainder.  
 6  Transfer fixed principal amount; issue check for remainder.  
 7  Renew the fixed principal amount and externally transfer the remainder.  
 8  Externally transfer the fixed principal amount and renew the remainder.  
 9  Issue a check for the fixed principal amount and externally transfer the remainder.  
 A  Externally transfer the fixed principal amount and issue a check for the remainder.

TmeLvlIntExtTrsfrAbaNbr.description: Identifies the organization receiving the interest external transfer.

DPNewCDFixedPrinAmt.description: The amount of principal to be renewed or distributed.  This amount cannot exceed the principal balance of the time deposit.  This amount must be zero if the principal disposition is set to 0 and must be greater than zero if the principal disposition is set to 5 or 6.

DPNewCDAcctNbr.description: Deposit System account number.  For retirement accounts, enter either the account number or the retirement plan    number.

DLTNCOvrideErrLvlInd.description:
Used only if using the automatic security override method of exception handling.  See Remarks section for further information on automatic versus selective security override.  
 1  Automatically override any edits up to operator alerts.  
 2  Automatically override any edits up to those requiring operator override.  
 3  Automatically override any edits up to those requiring supervisor override.

DPNewCDRnwlCde.description:
Indicates possible renewal of certificate at maturity.  This field can default to Bank Control.  
 N  Renewable at new rate.  
 O  Renewable at old rate. 
 P  Renew at new rate, new penalty calculation and renewal code.  
 X  Nonrenewable.  
 I  Renew at new interest plan values.

DPNewCDIntTrsfrToAcct.description: Indicates the account to which interest is transferred.

DPNewCDIntCalcMeth.description:
Method for calculating interest.  This field can default to Bank Control.  
 C  Continuous compounding.  
 D  Daily compounding.  
 O  S&P 500.  
 P  Pure simple.  
 S  Daily simple.

TmeLvlIntExtTypCde.description:

 D  Deposit account.  
 G  General ledger account.  
 L  Loan account.  
 S  Savings account.

 Y  Waive service charge.

DPStpPmtIndivID.description: For an ACH item, the individual identification.  The number assigned for identification of a particular person on the system of record.  Could contain social security number.

BlkflInd.description:
Controls how the physical items are sorted and filed after posting and whether they are returned to the customer in the statement.
 
 A  Auto pay indicator. Bulk filed and returned with statement; exception reasons are passed from the Deposit System and processed based on the item processing vendor.  
 B  Bulk filed and returned with statement; exception reasons cause items to outsort.  
 C  Fine sorted daily and returned with statement.  
 I  Image file.  Note: This option is only for institutions using image statements.  If this option is selected, additional programming is required.  Contact your account manager for a programming estimate.  
 N  Bulk file with cycle sort.  
 P  Currently not used.  
 T  Truncated file; not returned with statement (check safekeeping).  
 Blank Bulk file with cycle sort.  
 
 Note: When the BULKFILE indicator is set to A, B, or I, closing statements are produced on the next statement date.  In all other cases, the closing statement is produced on the closing date.  Also, a bulk file account will not purge if the next statement date is greater than the purge date.

ChrgNoChrgInd.description:
Indicates the disbursement of service charges for this account.
 
 0  No analysis charges, if under age limit.  Charges are deferred and listed on the Service Charge Referrals report (R-2810).  Any action to be taken would be manual. Direct charges post to the account.  
 1  Charge-current.  
 2  Deferred.  Analysis charges are deferred and listed on the Service Charge Referrals report (R-2810).  Any action to be taken would be manual.  Direct charges post to the account.  
 3  Referral. Analysis charges are deferred and listed on the Service Charge Referrals report (R-2810).  Any action to be taken would be manual.  Direct charges post to the account.  
 4  Billing.  Analysis charges are deferred and listed on the Service Charge Referrals report (R-2810).  Any action to be taken would be manual.  Direct charges post to the account.  
 5  Waive analysis.  Analysis charges are deferred and listed on the Service Charge Referrals report (R-2810).  Any action to be taken would be manual.  Direct charges post to the account.  
 6  Waive direct and analysis (analysis refers to Deposit System analysis fees and not Account Analysis System analysis fees).  
 7  Waive direct.  Direct charges are waived.  Any action to be taken would be manual.  Analysis charges post to the account.  
 
 Note: Selecting Charge/No Charge Code 6 (waive direct and analysis) causes a direct default charge to default to waive and an analysis default charge to default to analysis on Online Exceptions and Exceptions Desktop.  Selecting Charge/No Charge Code 7 (waive direct) causes a default direct charge on Online Exceptions and Exceptions Desktop to default to waive.
